    <item>
      <title> Swap two lines</title>
      <link>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/vim/swap-lines/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Nov 2016 00:58:50 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/vim/swap-lines/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h4 id=&#34;swap-the-current-line-with-the-previous&#34;&gt;Swap the current line with the previous&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;ddkP
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;dd&lt;/code&gt; - Cut current line&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;k&lt;/code&gt; - Move one line upwards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;P&lt;/code&gt; - Paste before the cursor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;swap-the-current-line-with-the-next&#34;&gt;Swap the current line with the next&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;ddp
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;dd&lt;/code&gt; - Cut current line&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;p&lt;/code&gt; - Paste&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Setting environment variables (command line)</title>
      <link>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/windows/set-environment-variables/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Nov 2016 00:40:33 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/windows/set-environment-variables/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h3 id=&#34;set-environment-variables-in-the-current-prompt&#34;&gt;Set environment variables in the current prompt.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ps&#34;&gt;set NODE_ENV=development
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;notices note&#34; &gt;&lt;p&gt;set.exe does not set the environment variable in subsequent command prompts. The variables are only available in the currently opened prompt.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3 id=&#34;set-persistent-environment-variables&#34;&gt;Set persistent environment variables&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ps&#34;&gt;setx NODE_ENV=development
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;notices note&#34; &gt;&lt;p&gt;setx.exe does not set the environment variable in the current command prompt, but it will be available in subsequent command prompts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3 id=&#34;list-all-environment-variables&#34;&gt;List all environment variables&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ps&#34;&gt;set
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ps&#34;&gt;ALLUSERSPROFILE=C:\ProgramData
APPDATA=C:\Users\user\AppData\Roaming
.
.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
